==Greek==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|el|grc|γράφω}}, from {{inh|el|grk-pro|*grəpʰō}}, from {{der|el|ine-pro|*gerbʰ-}}. For the stems, see ''[[#Related terms|Related terms]]''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|el|/ˈɣra.fo/}}
* {{hyphenation|el|γρά|φω}}

===Verb===
{{el-verb|past=έγραψα|passive=γράφομαι}}

# to [[write]], [[pen]]
#: {{ux|el|'''Γράφετε''' βιβλίο;|t=Are you '''writing''' a book?}}
# to [[record]]
# to [[issue]] a [[ticket]] {{q|for traffic violation, etc}}

====Conjugation====
{{el-conjug-1st
|augmented=1
|present=γράφ
|a-imperfect=έγραφ
|a-dependent=γράψ
|a-simplepast=έγραψ
|p-imperfect=γραφ
|p-dependent=γραφτ
|p-dependent-2=γραφ
|p-simplepast=γράφτ
|p-simplepast-2=γράφ
|p-perf-part=γραμ
|cat=γράφω
<!-- + colloquial imperatives -->
|a-impv-ps=[[γράψε]], [[γράφ']]&nbsp;<sup>1</sup>
|a-impv-pp=[[γράψτε]], [[γράφτε]]<sup>2</sup>
|note1=Colloquial {{glossary|apocopic}} perfective imperative + accusative of article & noun or {{glossary|weak pronoun|weak pronouns}} e.g. '''γράφ' [[το#Pronoun|το]]''' ("write it!"). Compare to imperfective '''γράφε το''' ("keep writing it")
|note2=Colloquial form: [[γράφτε]]. There is also a formal type: [[γράψετε]].
